HEADWORD: Scutcher
<hw>Scutch"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
scutches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An implement or machine for scutching hemp, flax, or
cotton, etc.; a scutch; a scutching machine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutch grass</ent>⟦br⟧
